Summary of ASX Announcement (PTN - Patronus Resources)

Material Information for Trading/Capital Markets Decisions:

  • New High-Grade Gold Discovery:
  • High-grade gold shoot discovered at Merlin Prospect, extending over 450m strike.

  • Located 400m north of existing 138,000oz Mertondale 3-4/North Resource.

  • Drilling Results (12-hole RC program, 1,698m):

  • MT25RC007: 10m @ 2.10g/t Au from 94m.
  • MT25RC008: 24m @ 1.16g/t Au from 61m.

  • MT25RC006: 10m @ 1.24g/t Au from 76m.

  • Exploration Upside:

  • Mineralization remains open down-dip and along strike.

  • Follow-up RC drilling and metallurgical test work planned for Q3/Q4 2025.

  • Strategic Context:

  • Merlin lies within the 12km Mertondale East Shear Zone, a highly prospective corridor.
  • Potential to expand the 1Moz Cardinia Gold Project.

Next Steps:

  • Additional drilling to test high-grade extensions.
  • Initial metallurgical test work in Q4 2025.

Material Information Extraction:

Announcement Type: Exploration Results (Copper-Gold-Cobalt Mineralisation)

Key Highlights:

  • New Mineralisation Discovered: Significant Cu-Au-Co intercepts outside current resource boundaries at GAM (Great Australia Mine):
  • Copperhead Corridor:
    • 14m @ 0.81% Cu, 0.12g/t Au, 749ppm Co (CHRC001) including 6m @ 1.37% Cu.
    • 11m @ 0.45% Cu, 0.08g/t Au, 171ppm Co (CHRC005).
    • Extends mineralisation 350m beyond known resource.
  • Coppermine Creek: First-ever drill intercept (12m @ 0.65% Cu, 0.16g/t Au).
  • Paddock Lode South: 6m @ 0.63% Cu (70–100m southwest of current resource).
  • Orphan Shear: High-grade oxidised copper (9m @ 0.83% Cu, 521ppm Co).

Implications:

  • Resource Expansion Potential: Confirms continuity of mineralisation, enabling future resource upgrades.
  • Exploration Strategy: Follow-up drilling planned at Copperhead, Coppermine Creek, and Orphan Shear.

Next Steps:

  • Downhole EM surveys and 3D IP remodelling to refine targets.
  • Resource definition drilling at Copperhead and Paddock South.

Appendix 1 (JORC Table 1): Confirms standard sampling/QAQC protocols. No material deviations noted.

Valuation Impact: Positive for near-term resource growth and mine life extension.

Material Information Summary (ASX:CYL - Trident Drilling Update)

Key Highlights:

  • Trident Project Development:
  • Final approvals received for development; early works and expenditure have commenced.
  • First ore expected H2 CY2025.

  • Open pit mining approval secured (May 2025), reducing upfront capital to A$15m (offset by cashflows from 6koz open-pit production at A$3,200/oz gold prices).

  • Resource & Reserve:

  • Underground Resource: 508koz @ 3.7 g/t Au (2023) + 182koz @ 4.7 g/t Au (2024).
  • Probable Reserves: 1.3Mt @ 4.4 g/t Au (188koz).

  • Targeting conversion of 251koz Inferred → Indicated to extend mine life beyond initial 5-year plan (37koz pa average production).

  • Drilling Results:

  • 41 infill holes targeting Inferred Resources (200–350m depth); results confirm expected mineralization.
  • High-grade intercepts (e.g., 7.0m @ 15.5g/t, 4.2m @ 19.9g/t).

  • Potential to upgrade Resources; further results pending.

  • Capital & Liquidity:

  • Closing cash & bullion: A$98m; no debt.
  • Shares outstanding: 252m.

Catalyst Metals Overview:

  • Plutonic Gold Belt: 40km-long hosting 85koz pa production (AISC: A$2,192/oz).
  • Growth Pipeline: Three low-capex projects (total A$31m) feeding existing underutilized plant.

Material Information Summary (Canterbury Resources – Briggs Drilling & Scoping Study Update)

Key Highlights:

  • Deep Drilling Program:
  • 900m diamond drill hole planned for July 2025, targeting a high-priority VTEM geophysical anomaly southwest of the existing Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE).
  • VTEM target suggests potential for higher-grade copper sulphide mineralisation at depth.

  • Funded partially by a $250k (+GST) Queensland Government grant.

  • Briggs Scoping Study:

  • On track for completion in August 2025.
  • Evaluating a large-scale open-pit copper mine with conventional processing (crushing/flotation).

  • Current MRE (0.15% Cu cut-off): 2.0Mt Cu, 73Mlb Mo, 16.5Moz Ag.

  • Additional Drilling Planned:

  • Infill drilling later in 2025 to upgrade MRE confidence.

  • Further exploration contingent on deep drill results.

  • Resource Context:

  • Briggs is among Australia’s largest undeveloped copper projects.

Capital Markets Relevance:

  • No new capital raising or equity actions announced.
